==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic *''dil-'', from Indo-European *''dhēy-'' ‘suckle’.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Norse [[dilkr]] (dialectal Swedish [[del]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[θήσατο]], Latin [[femina]], Russian [[доить]], Latvian [[det]], Breton [[denaff]] ‘suck’.

